{
  "texts": [
    "The authors request further research to characterize risks that emerge from LLMs generally and across different language models to guide the development of these models in safer directions.",
    "The authors also report working on these types of evaluations, often in collaboration with other research groups, focusing on assessing risky emergent behaviors.",
    "However, this is not easy to conduct in practice without disseminating details surrounding the training data, model architecture, and associated training processes.",
    "While this information may be shared with these specific groups, whether one group can fully evaluate a model for all these biases must be questioned and, if they should, requires further deliberation.",
    "The complexity of biases encoded in algorithms is often far beyond what one group can identify; thus, a citizen science or open science approach may be more beneficial."
  ]
}